node.text:
Italy in Dubai 🍋
•
Staying in Dubai this summer and craving Italian food? Brunch at @bice_dubai is the answer! 🇮🇹
•
As you may know I spend a lot of my time in Italy and I LOVE Italian food, so Bice is one of my go to restaurants in Dubai for many years now!
Looking for authentic and high quality Italian food and a great atmosphere this weekend? 
Go to their Friday brunch where you can taste everything from traditional appetizers to delicious pizza and pasta 🍕🍝
Oh and don't forget to order an aperol spritz or prosecco, like the Italians do cheers!🍹🥂

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Manon Isabella on July 07, 2021 tagging @thetastingclass, @stagsleapwinecellars, @firstpourdrinks, and @california.vines.uae. May be an image of food and indoor.

node.text:
Wednesday = Wine Day 
•
I am super excited for tonight's tasting of Aveta Sauvignon Blanc from @stagsleapwinecellars together with @california.vines.uae and hosted by the lovely team of @thetastingclass 
An elegant and refreshing Sauvignon Blanc driven by citrus, orange blossom and guava fruit notes. 
Perfect for the summer! ☀
•
Grab your bottle from @mmidubai and join us tonight at 19.00 here on Instagram for the virtual tasting!
•
Some interesting info on the wine:
- @stagsleapwinecellars are using top notch fruit and have employed some unique techniques to give the wine more body, richness and texture
- they have the grapes crushed and the skins and juice sat oaked together for 3 days, when normally you press and ferment
- sauvignon blanc is generally unoaked, but this one was aged for 6 months on 20% new and 50% neutral French oak barrels, 30% stainless
